Hi,

recently I noticed in one of my crawls these kinds of URLs with a 
leading double slash.
I never saw this before but after some research I read that this can and 
will be used to inherit the protocol.
Heritrix handles these urls the same as it would be a relative path 
which leads of course to a 404 error.
e.g. http://de.wikipedia.org//ace.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kawan:Afrika

So my question is if this there is a reason that this is not implemented 
and what would be the best place to implement it in your opinion?
My first idea was to fix this probably inside the ExctractorHTML Module 
where the new URLs are extracted.

Thanks,
Markus



